---
import Container from "../components/Container.astro";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Label from "../components/Label.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms & Conditions"
  description="The terms for using BUT. Honestly: how the content is licensed, what you can reuse, and the usual disclaimers."
>
  <Container section id="terms" className="md:max-w-2xl">
    <Label>Terms &amp; Conditions</Label>
    <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl">Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>

    <p class="mt-5">
      The short version: read anything, learn anything, reuse the writing and
      the code within the licenses below, and don't expect any guarantees. Using
      this site means you're OK with what follows.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl">Who runs this</h2>
    <p class="mt-4">
      BUT. Honestly is a personal site written and maintained by Nicola Mustone
      (“Nico”). The opinions here are mine, not those of my employer or anyone
      else.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl">Using the site</h2>
    <p class="mt-4">
      Everything is free to read, with no account and no sign-up. Please don't
      use the site in ways that break it or others' use of it — automated
      scraping that hammers the server, attempts to probe or compromise it, or
      anything unlawful. It's a small site run by one person; treat it kindly.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl">Licensing &amp; reuse</h2>
    <p class="mt-4">
      Different parts of the site carry different licenses, so you always know
      what you're allowed to do:
    </p>
    <ul class="text-body mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
      <li>
        <strong>Articles, essays, and images</strong> are licensed under&nbsp;
        <a
          href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          >Creative Commons Attribution–NonCommercial–ShareAlike 4.0</a
        >. You may share and adapt them for non-commercial purposes, with credit
        and a link back, and share any derivative under the same license.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Code snippets and downloadable code</strong> are released under the&nbsp;
        <a
          href="https://www.gnu.org/licenses/old-licenses/gpl-2.0.html"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener">GNU General Public License v2 or later</a
        >. Use them in your own projects on those terms.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>The site's own source code</strong> is available under the MIT license.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mt-4">
      Trademarks, logos, and product names mentioned here belong to their
      respective owners and are used for reference only.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl">Code &amp; tutorials — use at your own risk</h2>
    <p class="mt-4">
      The tutorials, snippets, and tools here are provided as-is, for learning.
      Always test on a staging site and keep backups before running anything
      against a live site or store. I can't be responsible for data loss,
      downtime, or other consequences from using the code.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl">External links</h2>
    <p class="mt-4">
      Posts link to other sites and services I find useful. I don't control
      those sites and I'm not responsible for their content, availability, or
      practices.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl">No warranty</h2>
    <p class="mt-4">
      The site and its content are provided “as is,” without warranties of any
      kind, express or implied. I do my best to keep things accurate and up to
      date, but I don't guarantee that everything is complete, current, or
      error-free.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl">Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p class="mt-4">
      To the extent permitted by law, I won't be liable for any damages arising
      from your use of — or inability to use — this site or anything you find on
      it.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl">Changes</h2>
    <p class="mt-4">
      These terms may change as the site evolves. The current version always
      lives at this URL, with the date below.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 text-2xl">Contact</h2>
    <p class="mt-4">
      Questions about any of this? Reach me through any of the links in the
      footer.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-10 text-xs">Last updated: July 2026</p>
  </Container>
</Layout>
